        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 28 at 2:16PM EDT by NWS Wilmington NC</headline>
        <description>At 216 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Little Rock, or near Dillon. This thunderstorm was nearly stationary.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Dillon, Bingham, Hamer, South Of The Border, Little Rock, Minturn,
and Mcleod Medical Center.

This includes Interstate 95 in South Carolina between mile markers
187 and 198.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
